items.title: Will President Trump's Tariffs Cause the S&P 500 to Plunge? Here's What 1 Top Wall Street Analyst Thinks.
items.author: Keith Speights
items.description: Goldman Sachs projects that S&P 500 earnings and performance could be negatively impacted by President Trump's tariffs, with a potential 5% decline in the near term. However, the uncertainty created by tariffs could have a greater impact than the direct earnings effects.

insights.sentiment_reasoning: The article cites analysis from Goldman Sachs' chief U.S. equity strategist David Kostin, who provided estimates on the potential impact of tariffs on S&P 500 earnings and performance.
